      <div style=3D"max-width: 880px;">
        <div class=3D"lead">
          <p><a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/blog/why-sales-tax-can-vary-=
from-product-to-product">State and local sales tax rates vary from product =
to product</a>, but are not always applied to services =E2=80=93 it depends=
 on the type of service and the state. For more information on calculating =
sales tax rates, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/how-to-calcula=
te-sales-tax">this post</a> offers more information. Keep in mind that sale=
s tax rates (and laws) are always changing, so the best way to stay on top =
of things is to use TaxJar, which will help you charge the right amount of =
sales tax every time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

              <ul class=3D"accordion-list">
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-0">
            <details open=3D"">
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">Who should collect sales tax?</s=
pan>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p>If your business has offices, warehouses and employees i=
n a state, you likely have physical nexus, which means you=E2=80=99ll need =
to collect and file sales tax in that state. For more information on nexus,=
 <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/nexus">this blog post can assi=
st</a>. If you sell products to states where you do not have a physical pre=
sence, you may still have sales tax liability there =E2=80=93 and therefore=
 need to collect and remit taxes in that state. Every state has different s=
ales and transaction thresholds that trigger tax obligations for your busin=
ess =E2=80=93 <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/economic-nexus">t=
ake a look at this article</a> to find out what those thresholds are for th=
e states you sell to.</p>
<p>If your company is doing business with a buyer claiming a sales tax exem=
ption, you may have to deal with documentation involving customer exemption=
 certificates. To make matters more complicated, many states have their own=
 requirements for documentation regarding these sales tax exemptions. To ea=
se the pain, we=E2=80=99ve created an article that lists each state=E2=80=
=99s requirements, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/blog/file/tax-exemptio=
n-certificate">which you can find here</a>.</p>
<p>You should not collect sales tax from retail sales in a state before you=
 have registered for a sales tax permit. (If you=E2=80=99re looking for sal=
es tax rates in every state, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/resources/sa=
les-tax/states">we=E2=80=99ve provided them here</a>.) In general, the step=
s you should take to register with a state to collect sales tax are as foll=
ows: gather your EIN or other business identifying information, visit your =
state=E2=80=99s department of revenue website, click on the =E2=80=9CSales =
and Use Tax=E2=80=9D section of the site, and register your business. We=E2=
=80=99ve created a handy guide to lead you through the <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.taxjar.com/sales-tax/permits">steps to register for every state right he=
re</a>.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-1">
            <details>
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">How can I find a GST and VAT rat=
e?</span>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">We recommend using Stri=
pe=E2=80=99s </span><a href=3D"https://stripe.com/guides/tools/vat-calculat=
or" target=3D"_blank"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">VAT calculator</span=
></a><span style=3D"font-weight: 400"> or </span><a href=3D"https://stripe.=
com/guides/tools/gst-calculator" target=3D"_blank"><span style=3D"font-weig=
ht: 400">GST calculator</span></a><span style=3D"font-weight: 400"> to find=
 the correct GST or VAT rate.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/about?utm_medium=3Dwebsite&amp;utm_sou=
rce=3Dblog&amp;utm_content=3Dfive_steps_international&amp;utm_campaign=3Dab=
out-us"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Stripe acquired TaxJar</span></a><=
span style=3D"font-weight: 400"> in 2021 to accelerate the future of e-comm=
erce. Available in over 100 countries, Stripe Tax enables you to automatica=
lly calculate and collect the right amount of tax based on where you are re=
gistered, where your customers are located, and what you are selling. Strip=
e Tax also helps you monitor your obligations and provides reporting for fi=
ling and remittance. Learn more about Stripe Tax </span><a href=3D"https://=
stripe.com/tax" target=3D"_blank"><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">here</sp=
an></a><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-2">
            <details>
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">Do I need to collect sales tax w=
hen selling online?</span>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p>The answer to most questions about sales tax is usually =
=E2=80=9Cit depends,=E2=80=9D and the answer to this particular question is=
 no different. If you=E2=80=99re a retailer that makes online sales, you on=
ly need to collect sales tax and file tax returns for states in which you h=
ave physical and economic nexus. (You can learn more about nexus <a href=3D=
"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/nexus">in this blog post</a>.) Wherever y=
ou have a physical presence in a state =E2=80=93 like offices, warehouses a=
nd employees =E2=80=93 you likely have physical nexus, which means you=E2=
=80=99ll need to collect and file sales tax on taxable goods and services i=
n that state.</p>
<p>Things get more complicated when you=E2=80=99re an online seller, becaus=
e you may have economic nexus (and thus, sales tax obligations to remit) in=
 multiple states. Every state has different thresholds that trigger tax obl=
igations for your business =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s important to understand w=
here you are in relation to those thresholds to know whether you have oblig=
ations in a particular state.</p>
<p>When you use TaxJar, it=E2=80=99s easy to track where you have (and wher=
e you may soon have) economic nexus using our <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar=
.com/product/nexus-insights">Economic Nexus Insights dashboard</a>. Another=
 way to see if your business meets the threshold for economic nexus is by u=
sing <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/economic-nexus">this helpf=
ul guide</a>. And if you=E2=80=99re looking for state sales tax rates, take=
 a look at our <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/resources/sales-tax/states=
">state guide to sales and use tax</a>.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-3">
            <details>
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">What is the sales tax in my area=
?</span>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p>The sales and use tax of any given item or service is th=
e combined rate of a state sales tax rate and any additional local sales ta=
xes levied by a county or city. Furthermore, there may be limited sales tax=
es called special taxing district rates to help raise money for publicly-fu=
nded ventures like new schools, parks or rail systems. That=E2=80=99s why t=
he sales tax rate on a retail sale in one town can differ from one located =
in a different town =E2=80=93 even if it=E2=80=99s close by.</p>
<p>You can calculate the sales and use tax rate in your area by entering an=
 address into our <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax-calculator">S=
ales Tax Calculator</a>. This will provide a <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.=
com/product/api">combined sales tax rate</a> for a location. For a look at =
sales tax rates of all 50 states, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/resourc=
es/sales-tax/states">we=E2=80=99ve designed an interactive map</a> to help =
you out. And lastly, if you=E2=80=99re looking for information on why sales=
 tax varies from product to product, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sale=
s-tax/why-sales-tax-can-vary-from-product-to-product">this article can assi=
st</a>.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-4">
            <details>
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">How often should I file sales ta=
x returns for my business?</span>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p>Filing frequency varies by both the state you=E2=80=99re=
 filing in and the size of your business. As a general rule of thumb, the m=
ore taxable revenue you generate in a state, the more often they want you t=
o file sales and use tax. Your filing frequency may start out quarterly, bu=
t <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/economic-nexus">if you hit a =
revenue threshold</a>, a state may decide you need to file monthly. If you =
need to register for a sales tax permit, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/=
sales-tax/permits">we=E2=80=99ve compiled all the info here</a>. And <a hre=
f=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/sales-tax/how-to-file-sales-tax-in-each-state">=
here=E2=80=99s a primer on how to file online and by mail</a> for every sta=
te.</p>
<p>If you=E2=80=99re approaching a due date and you need to file sales tax =
today, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/blog/file/2022-01-sales-tax-is-due=
-today-now-what">we=E2=80=99ve created a quick guide</a> on how exactly to =
get that done.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                    <li id=3D"faq-question-5">
            <details>
              <summary class=3D"item-summary">
                <span class=3D"item-title">What happens if you forget to co=
llect sales tax?</span>
              </summary>
              <div class=3D"item-content">
                <p>If you have sales and use tax liabilities =E2=80=93 and =
don=E2=80=99t collect sales tax and remit them to a state =E2=80=93 there a=
re real implications for having tax due. That includes paying interest and =
penalties on top of the state sales tax you owe. There=E2=80=99s also the p=
ossibility of criminal penalties, lawsuits and reputational damage. For mor=
e information on some of the negative outcomes for not collecting sales tax=
, <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/blog/2022-04-what-are-the-real-impacts-=
of-not-being-compliant">we=E2=80=99ve laid them out in a blog post here</a>=
.</p>
<p>Here=E2=80=99s the good news: TaxJar makes it easy to track where you ha=
ve (and where you may soon have) sales tax obligations using our <a href=3D=
"https://www.taxjar.com/product/nexus-insights">Economic Nexus Insights das=
hboard</a>. TaxJar=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.taxjar.com/product/auto=
file">AutoFile</a> can also automate filing sales tax returns on your compa=
ny=E2=80=99s behalf, so you never miss a filing date again.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </li>
                  </ul>
          </div>
  </section>

